org.gradoop.flink.model.impl.operators.matching.single.cypher.operators.join

Class ValueJoin

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gradoop.flink.model.impl.operators.matching.single.cypher.operators.join.ValueJoin
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PhysicalOperator

    public class ValueJoin
extends Object
implements PhysicalOperator
    This operator joins two possibly disjunct data sets by predicates only concerning properties. The predicates must include at least one isolated equality predicate e.g. 
       MATCH (a:Department), (b)-[:X]->(c:Person {name: "Max") WHERE a.prop = b.prop AND a.prop2 =
   b.prop2
    The result is always a new embedding with the following constraints.
    • new entries of the right embedding are always appended to the left embedding
    • all properties from the right side are appended to the properties of the left side
